00037 Expected (black dashed) and observed (red solid) 95\% CL excluded region in the plane of $m_{
inoone}$ vs. $m_{\stopone}$ , assuming $\mathcal{BR}(\stopone 	o t 
inoone) = 100$\%. In the region $m_b + m_W + m_{
inoone} < m_{\stopone} < m_t + m_{
inoone}$ the decay of the $\stopone$ involves a virtual top quark (three-body decay), while in the region $m_{\stopone} < m_b + m_W + m_{
inoone}$ it involves both a virtual top quark and a virtual $W$ boson (four-body decay). The $m_{	one} < 100$\,\GeV\ region for the three-body decay scenario is excluded by the search described in ref.~\cite{stop2L_8TeV}. Furthermore, the $m_{	one} < 78$\,\GeV\ region in the four-body scenario is excluded by the search in ref.~\cite{Heister:2002hp}.

